The paper deals with autonomous driving in an urban environment, which is a problem in robotics and falls under the category of Robotics and Control (cs.RO). The paper also discusses algorithms for localization and navigation, which involve computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques. The Monte Carlo studies and experiments involve statistical analysis and machine learning, which are covered under the categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Systems and Control (cs.SY).
